div.p:
Once when he was in dire and perilous circumstances the voice of God comforted him with
this assurance: "The ends of the earth shall inquire after thy name, and fools shall have thee
in derision, and hell shall rage against thee;

Further: To the newly established Church in this dispensation the Lord said, speaking of
Joseph Smith: ". . . thou shalt give heed unto all his words and commandments which he shall
give unto you as he receiveth them, walking in all holiness before me;
